# China Payment Standards

- Use this rule together with `payment.mdc` when editing China payment flows.
- Keep CN provider behavior in CN-specific files. Do not keep adding Alipay or WeChat Pay branches to Stripe-oriented modules.
- Treat provider callbacks, polling, and reconciliation as separate concerns. Notify handlers must be idempotent and backfill jobs must be safe to rerun.
- Store amounts in fen as integers. Validate recharge product IDs, amount, and user binding on the server.
- CN flows may be QR, native-app, or polling based. Do not force a redirect-only UX if the provider semantics differ.
- Keep CN pricing, currency, and payment copy aligned with the China deployment. Do not reuse global USD or Stripe-specific wording.
- Follow the credits-only model here too. CN can differ by provider availability, but not by introducing a separate subscription product model.
